The '''Rock Firefinch''' (''Lagonosticta sanguinodorsalis'') is a species of  found in northern . It has an estimated global extent of occurrence of 29,000 kmÂ².
The status of the species is evaluated as .
The Rock Firefinch has a blue-grey bill, red back in the male and reddish brown back in the female and juvenile and broad primaries in both the adult and juvenile.
 
It is commonly found in bushy and rocky outcrops on the  and inselbergs to the north and east. It probably feeds on grass seeds. 